This is the HIT integration test suite for hadoop DistCp 2.x release line.
In order to run the tests standalone:
  - yinst install -branch current hadoopdistcptest2dotX
  - $YROOT/bin/run-hadoopdistcp2dotX-integration-tests.sh -results-dir=<res> -logs-dir=<logs>

In order to run the tests in a hit environment:
  - deploy/enter a hit 2.x yroot
  - export COMP=hadoopdistcp2dotX
  - export HIT_LOG=/mnt/hit/results/`date +"%y%m%d%H%M"`
  - mkdir -p -m 0777 $HIT_LOG/$COMP/results $HIT_LOG/$COMP/logs
  - /home/y/bin/run-${COMP}-integration-tests.sh -results-dir=$HIT_LOG/${COMP}/results -logs-dir=$HIT_LOG/$COMP/logs > $HIT_LOG/$COMP/runlog

Notes:

Confirm that the following environment variables are correctly set for your installation:
- FIT_HDFS_STORAGE_DIR   -> your HDFS base URI
- HADOOP_COMMON_HOME     -> your hadoop install base path

Changes:

20130906 - initial create, main change is to use webhdfs and remove hftp since hftp is 
not officially supported in 2.x

